Durban - A 29-year-old man was sentenced to life in prison by the Umlazi Regional Court for the rape of a six-year-old child last week. Luvuyo Lukashe was convicted for a rape he committed  four years ago.

KwaZulu-Natal police spokesperson, Lieutenant Colonel Thulani Zwane, said on March 25, 2014, the child was playing at Umlazi area when she was approached by the accused. She was taken to the accused’s house where she was raped.AdChoicesADVERTISINGinRead invented by Teads

"The child was threatened not to tell anyone about the incident. The mother noticed that the child was behaving strangely and questioned her. The girl then reported the incident to her mother," Zwane said. 
He said a case of rape was opened at Umlazi police station for further investigation. 

Umlazi FCS took over investigation and two days later the accused was arrested and charged accordingly.

The accused made several court appearance until he was sentenced.

